 the negativity in death, language, drive, anxiety, visual perception, paternity, and the unconscious. Formulating one of the most theoretically rigorous readings of the Coens' oeuvre to date, Buckner also offers a readable overview of some central debates in late twentieth-century continental philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aCoen, Ethan -- Criticism and interpretation. 0aCoen, Joel -- Criticism and interpretation. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPsychology : Psychoanalysis. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845256240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438452562423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438452562/original  a978-3-11-149015-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles